                "name": "Cling",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex",
                "text": "If a creature leaves a tick swarm\u2019s square, the swarm takes 1d6 points of damage to reflect the loss of its numbers as several ticks cling to the victim. A creature with ticks clinging to it takes swarm damage at the end of its turn each round. As a full round action, the creature can remove the ticks with a DC 20 Reflex save. At least 10 points of damage from any area effect destroys all clinging ticks. The save DC is Dexterity-based."
            },
